users.bio:
Official Bio:
With his first computer program written in 1978 and his first software company making a profit before he could vote, Eric has a proven track record of entrepreneurial success. After working as a product manager and evangelist at Apple, he founded Zero G software, which was purchased by Rovi (now Tivo). Imagination Technologies claimed his next company, and then he founded ArcTouch, his third company, with Adam Fingerman.

ArcTouch Internal Bio:
Eric started ArcTouch with his best friend and university roommate, Adam Fingerman, back in 2008 so that he'd have someone to geek out with and play with the latest technologies.  "I want an iPhone. Let's start a company so we can write it off."  Now, although he spends time focusing on financial and operational issues a lot of the time, he still gets excited to show off the latest cool things ArcTouch makes. His favorite ArcTouch apps of all time are the official Star Trek app, ABC Song, Pong, Yahoo Flickr and Weather, I Saw The Tooth Fairy, and ABC/Disney's Watch Disney JR... all because his kids have them installed on their own devices and use them all the time. (Even Star Trek.)

In his spare time, he likes to take things apart and fix them (they rarely go back together as they started), ski, and sail.  But, with 4 and 7 year old kids at home, along with two dogs (one is a puppy), and his wife... there's really not a lot of free time.
